Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.75,0:00:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.37,0:00:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.23,0:00:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the\Nlemon pie conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.09,0:00:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fragrant memories\Nand tender first love!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.13,0:00:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.88,0:00:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were invited to the\Nbirthday party of Uchida Asami,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.25,0:01:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rumored to have\Nbeen Shinichi's first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:02:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell asleep, so the rest of us\Nwent to the Karaoke Room in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.39,0:02:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when one of her friends\Nnoticed the lodge was on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uchida Asami\Nwas asleep in the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.73,0:02:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luckily, Ran broke down the\Ndoor and managed to save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Memories of First Love Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! She said that in her sleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I was saying, she was sleep-mumbling\Nwhen they brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm sorry! I'm sorry,\NKudo-{\i1}kun{\i0}! I'm so sorry!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.56,0:02:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?\NThat's just what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.57,0:03:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, are you thirsty?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.49,0:03:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can get you something from\Nthe vending machine downstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come with you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.54,0:03:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, is Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! He's perfectly okay!\NNot a scratch on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.25,0:03:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's with your dad,\Nloitering around the scene of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.19,0:03:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it really an accident? Did they\Njust forget to put out the candles?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then why was she asleep\Non the sofa when we left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but on the floor during the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.66,0:03:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something seems off about\Nthe furniture before and after the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost as if someone moved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?! Did someone\Ncome back here to set the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.21,0:04:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then Morimoto-{\i1}san {\i0}would be\Nmost suspicious, as he had the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.55,0:04:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone could've easily entered\Nvia a window unlocked in advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think! Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the witnesses,\Nthe fire started around 2:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.69,0:04:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the karaoke booth at 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.61,0:04:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By car, it'd take five minutes to get here.\NRunning, it'd take fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one was gone for thirty minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so only Noguchi-{\i1}san {\i0}could've\Ngone there, set the fire, and returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since he had the car key...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car was parked in\Nfront of the karaoke place,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and everyone left thirty minutes\Nbefore to use the station bathrooms
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and buy cigarettes and such\Nfrom the convenience store next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So someone would've\Nnoticed if the car was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not the car... Chika-{\i1}san{\i0}'s motorcycle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was parked in front of\Nthe lodge when we rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of the people in the\Nkaraoke booth could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.70,0:05:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be a different story if there\Nwas a timer device of some sort,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if there had been one,\Nthe firemen would've found it long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves what the old guy\Nsaid... It was Asami-{\i1}san {\i0}who...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you shouldn't be in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. I hear today's the\Nbirthday of that girl who was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.97,0:05:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The presents and the cake all\Nburned up, but this survived the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a birthday message for her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go give it to her at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? They don't fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.65,0:05:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.99,0:05:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that person\Ndid say something strange then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.41,0:05:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Of course there was a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cake with the lit candles\Nwas sitting on a chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mister. Was the\Ncake really on a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The chair was burnt up,\Nand the cake turned to goop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where was this chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.97,0:06:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.01,0:06:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of that small,\Ncharred cabinet in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't it\Nseem strange to you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she was in the tennis club\Nuntil her 2nd year of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.32,0:06:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she was the national champion that year!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.99,0:06:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But wasn't she the soccer\Nclub manager in her 3rd year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.75,0:06:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Apparently she completely\Nchanged after that summer break!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably wanted to\Nfocus on her studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that'd be even weirder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The 2nd semester of the 3rd\Nyear is when people quit their clubs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:06:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange, now that you mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she switched 'cause there\Nwere no hot guys in the tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.52,0:07:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right. She isn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyways,\Nshe must've had her reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.61,0:07:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably\Nnone of our business to pry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.15,0:07:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wanna know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}S-Senpai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Customers who\Ncame in at around 3:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Do you remember who came?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.92,0:07:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think. Just some youngsters\Ndoing karaoke next door, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They bought cigarettes,\Ntomato juice, and other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.60,0:07:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were they like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A brown-haired guy with\Nglasses, a girl in a black dress,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.65,0:07:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a guy with a buzz-cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sawai-{\i1}san{\i0}, Hayasaka-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nand Noguchi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh! That buzz-cut guy\Npuked in front of the store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.45,0:07:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning it up was such a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:07:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mister. Could you tell me if...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.79,0:08:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko! Any luck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.46,0:08:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she wasn't in the bathroom.\NHow about you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No luck here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.22,0:08:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Asami-{\i1}senpai {\i0}have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just contact your dad\Nfor now! I'll go get a nurse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right, little boy!\NHow did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.61,0:08:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him he had it backwards,\Nbut he didn't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had sticky stuff on it, too.\NWhat a ridiculous customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No question about it!\NThat person set the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if my theory is right, the\Nevidence is still in their possession!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.54,0:08:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! She was in\Nbed just a minute ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:09:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must've left while we were\Ngetting something to drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look around outside the\Nhospital! She might still be nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Asami have gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She may be planning to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.90,0:09:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If it really was\NAsami-{\i1}san {\i0}who set the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.37,0:09:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so one might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the truth is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.38,0:09:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}san {\i0}was not\Nthe perpetrator but the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Victim?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Asami-{\i1}san {\i0}was nearly burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By one of you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.19,0:10:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the fire started when\Nwe were in the karaoke booth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd take fifteen minutes\Nto run from there to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.04,0:10:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or only five minutes\Nby car or motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car didn't seem to have been used,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.71,0:10:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the motorcycle\Nwas parked by this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.00,0:10:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of us could have\Ncome here to set the fire then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it'd be different if there\Nwas some sort of timer device,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the firefighters would've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A timer device...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was something\Nnot out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was something\Nthat belonged there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.11,0:10:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and could be controlled\Nfrom a remote location?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The perpetrator set\Nthe fire from kilometers away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By using a certain thing at a\Ncertain location near the karaoke place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.17,0:10:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy! Everything's ready here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.71,0:10:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.97,0:11:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. What's ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.09,0:11:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This man asked me to have\Nthe firefighters set up the same trick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the bad guy used!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.39,0:11:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.81,0:11:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just such a surprisingly simple trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it'll make you laugh, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.82,0:11:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see. It's set up like\Nthe living room before the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It even has a fax machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how will this help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.46,0:11:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Conan to buy some just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we place it on the chair in front\Nof the fax machine, everything's set.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just wait until it starts a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uhh, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.40,0:12:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not suggesting we wait\Nuntil a candle falls to the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.12,0:12:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if that was what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that'd make it an accident\Ncaused by carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would hardly call--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.34,0:12:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's a fax!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.44,0:12:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That fax was sent by the convenience\Nstore owner at my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.41,0:12:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as the perpetrator sent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.91,0:12:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the perpetrator's intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.29,0:13:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more complicated the trick,\Nthe more likely evidence will be left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the idea was to simplify the trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,leave as little out of\Nthe ordinary as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make it look\Nlike an accidental fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.43,0:13:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.35,0:13:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went to the convenience\Nstore to buy cigarettes at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Sawai Manabu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You did it, Sawai-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true, right, President?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But he leapt into\Nthe flames to rescue Asami!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would he really rescue\Nsomeone he was trying to kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he was the first to notice the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he hadn't intended to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if this fire was set so\Nhe could rescue Asami-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sawai-{\i1}san {\i0}most likely did the following...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped sedatives into\Nher drink to make her sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.57,0:14:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,set up the trick just now while\Neveryone was getting ready to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.57,0:14:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then left the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.41,0:14:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep Asami-{\i1}san {\i0}from burning\Nto death, he placed her on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,far away from any furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, just as he planned,\Nwhile everyone was busy doing karaoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.17,0:14:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he sent a fax to\Nthe lodge and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.59,0:14:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The store owner saw him sending\Nthe fax just before the fire started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The burned remnants\Nof that fax were also found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.64,0:14:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burned remnants?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.81,0:14:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These! A firefighter gave them to me earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The shapes don't fit,\Nso there must've been two pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one page was sent before\Nthe fire, so it seemed strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.82,0:14:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.07,0:14:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, now! Yes, I did send\Na fax at the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.66,0:15:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a fax I sent to a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me to come\Nup with a good title for his novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? A friend, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.34,0:15:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do you explain the transmit slip?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.30,0:15:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gave the transmit slip to the\Nstore owner after you sent it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.73,0:15:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The date, time, phone number,\Nand your fingerprints are on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange.\NI'm sure I sent it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I must've dialed the wrong number!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? My friend's number and this\Nlodge's number are next to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm president of Toto\NUniversity's mystery study club!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.17,0:15:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never use such\Nan unreliable trick as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you tested it with a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.22,0:15:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you set up the living room trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you used the fax machine's copy feature
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to determine where it would catch fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, to use the copy\Nfeature, you need to use an original.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you copied the birthday\Nmessage Professor Takamura just sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which was lying nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, you faxed that copy\Nfrom the convenience store later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.29,0:16:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The copy that had the\Nmessage and cake cream on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The owner complained that you\Nstuck sticky paper in the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.10,0:16:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He also said he told you it was backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.18,0:16:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't blame him.\NYou sent the blank side of the copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.15,0:16:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if two faxes with the same\Nmessage were found at the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would raise suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough! I'm sick of these\Ngroundless, made-up accusations!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.95,0:17:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to make\Nsuch claims, show some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still playing innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the fax in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People certainly are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.17,0:17:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't easily throw away\Nanything that could put them in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They worry that\Nsomeone else might pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a prime example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even brought it back\Nfrom the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying he--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He should still\Nhave it on him somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fax with Professor Takamura's\Nmessage and cake cream on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.58,0:17:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.66,0:17:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How ridiculous! I should've\Njust thrown this thing away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then it really was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:18:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I set the fire. Using the exact\Nmethod the detective explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.43,0:18:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know it was me?\NAnyone could've used that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think back to when we all rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we call her on the phone?!\NShe was asleep in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.94,0:18:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! It's already burned up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Only someone who knew\Nwhere the fire was could've said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.99,0:18:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would you do that to Asami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted her to love me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.21,0:18:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a brave man who risked his\Nlife to rescue her from the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She turned me down\Nwhen I asked her out last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That had never happened\Nto me before, so I couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.64,0:18:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd planned for it to be a small fire,\Nbut it spread faster than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.35,0:18:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a small fire?!\NIt spread faster than you thought?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think those\Nserve as excuses?! You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't you imagine\NAsami-{\i1}san {\i0}possibly burning to death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car could've gotten into an accident!\NIt could've gotten a flat tire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.20,0:19:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There could've been a traffic jam!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}san {\i0}would've lost\Nher life in any of those cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted her to love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why didn't you consider becoming\Nsomeone who could be loved?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you consider\Nimproving yourself instead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That was very stupid, President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did something horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you did this for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. You can explain\Neverything to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't open people's hearts with force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.80,0:19:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you could capture any\Nman with a single breath, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't know about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.98,0:20:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, even I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.98,0:20:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...even I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You confessed to Shinichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.07,0:21:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. I was the one who confessed my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.03,0:21:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He completely rejected me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.50,0:21:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the rumor said...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.45,0:21:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I started that rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wanted him to\Nlike me. He was my first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.09,0:22:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he didn't seem to care about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.73,0:22:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, there's one thing I'd like to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.05,0:22:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly about him did you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.60,0:22:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. I didn't really\Ntake notice of him at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.25,0:22:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his first year, he was a regular\Nmidfielder on the soccer team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.73,0:22:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was an impressive\Nnewcomer. That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.24,0:22:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But one day, I shared some\Nlemon pie I made with the soccer club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone told me it\Nwas delicious, except for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.44,0:22:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This is kind of bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.54,0:22:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi has a weird sense of taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I guess it really wasn't very good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.13,0:22:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later on, everyone\Nsaid they had pretended to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.35,0:22:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt my feelings, so I baked\Na new one every day for three months
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.73,0:22:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until he said it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.11,0:23:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I was\Nmanager of the soccer club
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.72,0:23:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and fascinated with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone else made it\Ngreat on her first try, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.72,0:23:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know? I was mean and\Ntaught you a weird way of making it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.82,0:23:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! How come?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.23,0:23:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. Shall I tell you what he\Nsaid after I confessed to him, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.29,0:23:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Umm, say--!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.50,0:23:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pipe down!\NThis is getting good! Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.66,0:23:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said this while\Nacting embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.64,0:23:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, {\i1}Senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.39,0:23:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone I've been\Nfond of since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.31,0:23:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's strong-minded and obstinate,\Nyet easily moved to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.31,0:23:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that strangeness of hers...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.80,0:23:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.89,0:23:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, Ran! Could that be--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.63,0:23:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember a girl like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.61,0:23:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.55,0:23:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.71,0:24:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb, Okita!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.79,0:24:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw Nagakura Isami-{\i1}san\N{\i0}collapse on the veranda from your room!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.85,0:24:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It definitely looks\Nlike Okita-{\i1}san {\i0}killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.79,0:24:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NCould this incident be--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.80,0:24:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Historical Drama\NActor Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.90,0:24:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.54,0:24:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.66,0:24:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is a historical drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.32,0:24:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sekai Marumie!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.40,0:24:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.55,0:24:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.66,0:24:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
